0second%20offer%20typically%20pays%20out%20less%20than%20the%20first%2C%20the%20drivers%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUber's%20product%20chief%20said%20on%20social%20media%20that%20the%20fare%20discrepancies%20were%20a%20glitch.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20said%20a%20bug%20caused%20its%20app%20to%20drive%20down%20payouts%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-student-shares-uber-lyft-side-hustle-gig-work-struggles-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20some%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fare%20discrepancies%20happened%20on%20Trip%20Radar%2C%20a%20feature%20that%20Uber%20introduced%20four%20years%20ago%20that%20offers%20a%20gig%20to%20multiple%20drivers%20at%20once%2C%20often%20as%20they're%20finishing%20up%20another%20ride.%20Since%20they're%20competing%20with%20other%20drivers%20to%20claim%20the%20trip%2C%20it's%20common%20for%20drivers%20to%20accept%20a%20ride%20but%20not%20get%20it%20because%20someone%20else%20accepted%20it%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20month%20or%20so%2C%20three%20drivers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20have%20started%20getting%20a%20follow-up%20offer%3A%20the%20same%20trip%20with%20the%20same%20route%20they%20previously%20accepted%2C%20but%20at%20a%20lower%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20X%2C%20a%20driver%20posted%20screenshots%20from%20one%20such%20trip.%20Uber%20initially%20offered%20the%20driver%20%2412.53%20for%20a%20ride%20of%20just%20under%20six%20miles%20%E2%80%94%20then%20the%20offer%20fell%20to%20%2411.60%20on%20the%20second%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHere%20we%20go%20again.%20Since%20the%20rideshare%2